==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Blotting paper
<hw>Blot"ting pa`per</hw> <pr>(p⟦amac⟧`p⟦etil⟧r)</pr>. <def>A kind of
thick, bibulous, unsized paper, used to absorb superfluous ink from a
freshly written manuscript, and thus prevent blots.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>blotto</ent>⟦br⟧
